                {
                    "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/issue/13398300/comment/17407208",
                    "id": "17407208",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=apitrou",
                        "name": "apitrou",
                        "key": "pitrou",
                        "avatarUrls": {
                            "48x48": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?ownerId=pitrou&avatarId=35049",
                            "24x24": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&ownerId=pitrou&avatarId=35049",
                            "16x16": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&ownerId=pitrou&avatarId=35049",
                            "32x32": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&ownerId=pitrou&avatarId=35049"
                        },
                        "displayName": "Antoine Pitrou",
                        "active": true,
                        "timeZone": "Europe/Paris"
                    },
                    "body": "Our integer division returns an integer, so that's not possible. You can cast to float first if you want to get a float result.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=apitrou",
                        "name": "apitrou",
                        "key": "pitrou",
                        "avatarUrls": {
                            "48x48": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?ownerId=pitrou&avatarId=35049",
                            "24x24": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&ownerId=pitrou&avatarId=35049",
                            "16x16": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&ownerId=pitrou&avatarId=35049",
                            "32x32": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&ownerId=pitrou&avatarId=35049"
                        },
                        "displayName": "Antoine Pitrou",
                        "active": true,
                        "timeZone": "Europe/Paris"
                    },
                    "created": "2021-08-31T09:50:49.380+0000",
                    "updated": "2021-08-31T09:50:49.380+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/issue/13398300/comment/17407270",
                    "id": "17407270",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=jorisvandenbossche",
                        "name": "jorisvandenbossche",
                        "key": "jorisvandenbossche",
                        "avatarUrls": {
                            "48x48": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452",
                            "24x24": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452",
                            "16x16": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452",
                            "32x32": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"
                        },
                        "displayName": "Joris Van den Bossche",
                        "active": true,
                        "timeZone": "Europe/Brussels"
                    },
                    "body": "I suppose that's also what R should (can?) do: cast to float first so you can get Inf? (without needing changes on the C++ side)\r\n\r\nNote that 0/0 will then give NaN. I don't know the details of R integers, but can they also contain NaN?",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=jorisvandenbossche",
                        "name": "jorisvandenbossche",
                        "key": "jorisvandenbossche",
                        "avatarUrls": {
                            "48x48": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452",
                            "24x24": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452",
                            "16x16": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452",
                            "32x32": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"
                        },
                        "displayName": "Joris Van den Bossche",
                        "active": true,
                        "timeZone": "Europe/Brussels"
                    },
                    "created": "2021-08-31T11:45:52.299+0000",
                    "updated": "2021-08-31T11:45:52.299+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/issue/13398300/comment/17407377",
                    "id": "17407377",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=npr",
                        "name": "npr",
                        "key": "npr",
                        "avatarUrls": {
                            "48x48": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=34045",
                            "24x24": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=34045",
                            "16x16": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=34045",
                            "32x32": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=34045"
                        },
                        "displayName": "Neal Richardson",
                        "active": true,
                        "timeZone": "America/Los_Angeles"
                    },
                    "body": "In both cases in R, you get promoted to double so you can hold Inf or NaN",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=npr",
                        "name": "npr",
                        "key": "npr",
                        "avatarUrls": {
                            "48x48": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=34045",
                            "24x24": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=34045",
                            "16x16": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=34045",
                            "32x32": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=34045"
                        },
                        "displayName": "Neal Richardson",
                        "active": true,
                        "timeZone": "America/Los_Angeles"
                    },
                    "created": "2021-08-31T14:14:26.807+0000",
                    "updated": "2021-08-31T14:14:26.807+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/issue/13398300/comment/17407383",
                    "id": "17407383",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=jorisvandenbossche",
                        "name": "jorisvandenbossche",
                        "key": "jorisvandenbossche",
                        "avatarUrls": {
                            "48x48": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452",
                            "24x24": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452",
                            "16x16": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452",
                            "32x32": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"
                        },
                        "displayName": "Joris Van den Bossche",
                        "active": true,
                        "timeZone": "Europe/Brussels"
                    },
                    "body": "But if division of integers always give double in R, you can also do this cast to float before dividing instead of setting an option in the division kernel to get this behaviour?  And if this is done in the R bindings, the R user sees the expected behaviour for float. \r\n\r\nBTW, also in pandas/numpy, division of integers results in float typed array. ",
